attributes.name: Biscotti | Live Resin Cart
attributes.body: Airo Brands puts the true-plant experience at the forefront with the Live Rosin Series. Live Rosin is full-spectrum, premium cannabis concentrate made from fresh-frozen cannabis plants. What makes Live Rosin different from Live Resin? Live Rosin is solventless, meaning no chemicals are used in the extraction process. It’s similar to Live Resin as it’s packed with full-spectrum cannabinoids and a robust terpene profile. The unique atomizer assembly is optimized for Live Rosin to preserve the maximum amount of terpenes. Each cartridge captures the distinctive characteristics of its strain – creating the most authentic flower-like experience in a vape. Live Rosin is extracted using all-natural processes. At the ideal plant maturity, plants are harvested and immediately frozen – which is the “live”. Then, the plants are placed in a rosin press. The press uses heat and pressure to extract a hot oil from the plants – which is the rosin. Easily find your new favorite cartridge with its distinct rose gold color. **AiroPod Cartridges are only compatible with the AiroPro and AiroSport Vaporizer.**

attributes.name: RSO | Syringe
attributes.body: What is RSO? Put simply, RSO is an oil derived from cannabis. But rather than a solvent extract that strips trichomes from buds, RSO contains all the cannabinoids, terpenes, and additional compounds of the whole cannabis plant. The extraction process is complex and fairly long, similar to making a tincture. It’s typically near-black in color, and, admittedly, doesn’t taste great due to its high amount of plant matter (it uses the whole plant). RSO was created as a medicinal therapeutic for cancer and other chronic health conditions, like MS and asthma. While Rick Simpson no longer produces the oil himself, it remains a crucial ingredient in the treatment plans of patients across North America.

attributes.name: Bluntz
attributes.body: Prohibition 37 flower is our specialty and what we have built our brand on. Our production facilities include 2 state-of-the-art indoor cultivations totaling 14,000 sq ft in our home city of Albuquerque. We also have an outdoor farm in Belen, and greenhouse productions in Belen and Gallup. Our mission is to destigmatize the industry, produce outstanding quality cannabis, and positively contribute to the quality of life of our patients and customers. We currently grow over 75 cultivars, and are continually adding the newest and most sought after genetics to bring to every corner of New Mexico. WHO IS P37? Prohibition 37 is a physician-led, nationally recognized, and award-winning vertical cannabis company. P37 is highly focused on the customer experience and science of the medicinal and recreational effects of its many products. Our name is derived from The Marihuana Tax Act of 1937, which was a U.S. federal law that effectively criminalized the possession and distribution of marijuana. While it did not directly ban the cannabis plant, it imposed strict regulations and heavy taxes on its cultivation, sales, and use. This made it impossible to legally engage in these activities, leading to a de facto prohibition of cannabis. The Act played a significant role in shaping the modern approach to marijuana regulation in the United States.\ SOCIAL EQUITY AND JUSTICE The Marihuana Tax Act of 1937 disproportionately targeted minorities, particularly African, Mexican, and Jewish American communities. While the act did not explicitly mention racial or ethnic groups, its implementation and enforcement were marked by tremendous racial bias and discrimination. Law enforcement, for example, selectively targeted and arrested individuals from minority groups and used marijuana-related offenses as a pretext for discriminatory actions. This contributed to the disproportionate impact of the Act on minorities, perpetuating racial stereotypes and injustices for generations to come. Our mission at Prohibition 37 is to reverse decades of cannabis-related injustice and create a healthy, communal, and scientific approach to cannabis use.

attributes.name: Purple Push Pop
attributes.body: Seed Junky started in the early 2000’s in a small garage in Southern California where JBeezy’s passion for growing and breeding cannabis started. As a hands-on cultivator, his relentless breeding and pheno-hunting led to the creation of Ice Cream Cake, Wedding Cake, Kush Mints,The Soap, Jealousy, and hundreds of other top shelf strains for several brands nationwide. Being a Seed Junky is a way of life - We are connected directly to cultivators and create genetics for the best in the game. We are now breeding and cultivating on a large scale with relentless pheno-hunts to reveal the hottest cultivars that check every box; terpenes, THC, large yields, and bursting flavors. We are committed to daily innovation and a relentless pursuit to bring new flavors to the market and spread the dank worldwide. Our mission is to provide a lifestyle culture to this industry by challenging the game, spreading our knowledge, and creating the best flavors and strains in the world. From tent growers to commercial operators, we are committed to providing quality genetics you can rely on.
